        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 7:11AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 710 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Pecks Pond, or 13 miles west of Montague, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dingmans Ferry, Pecks Pond, and Tamiment.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
